- Let me go!

609
00:45:49,100 --> 00:45:51,920
We have a history, so stop being like this.

610
00:45:51,920 --> 00:45:54,770
I'm just here to ask you about something.

611
00:45:54,770 --> 00:45:57,280
Let me go.

612
00:45:57,280 --> 00:46:00,510
Okay.

613
00:46:00,520 --> 00:46:04,430
Okay.

614
00:46:04,430 --> 00:46:07,880
Hey, Jo Sarah, let me ask just one question.

615
00:46:07,880 --> 00:46:14,130
The kid you gave birth to six years ago is my kid, right? This Jin Sang Goo's child.

616
00:46:14,130 --> 00:46:15,530
What?

617
00:46:15,530 --> 00:46:21,310
Back then... When we broke up... Were you... pregnant?

618
00:46:21,310 --> 00:46:24,110
You should've told me.

619
00:46:24,110 --> 00:46:27,050
Why did you give birth without letting me know?

620
00:46:27,050 --> 00:46:31,260
You crazy bastard.

621
00:46:31,260 --> 00:46:34,620
Jo Sarah, your hand still stings.

622
00:46:34,620 --> 00:46:41,530
Hey, Sarah, you might get in trouble treating me so roughly.

623
00:46:44,230 --> 00:46:48,670
Tell me before you go. Was that my child?

624
00:46:48,670 --> 00:46:54,530
I just need to know that. Somebody told me that they saw you heavily pregnant at a gynecologist.

625
00:46:56,470 --> 00:46:59,210
Hey, Jin Sang Goo.

626
00:47:01,930 --> 00:47:06,120
Why would I like a man who married another woman behind my back?

627
00:47:06,120 --> 00:47:09,370
A man who is so shameless?

628
00:47:09,370 --> 00:47:12,400
Why would I get pregnant and give birth for someone like you?

629
00:47:12,400 --> 00:47:14,120
Do you think I'm an idiot?

630
00:47:14,120 --> 00:47:20,400
Do you think I'm a fool? Why would I do such a crazy thing?

631
00:47:20,400 --> 00:47:23,510
So, you're saying that's not true?

632
00:47:23,510 --> 00:47:25,600
You're saying that friend was mistaken, right?

633
00:47:25,600 --> 00:47:29,650
Should I call your wife over here? Would you get away then?

634
00:47:29,650 --> 00:47:34,770
Okay, fine. I'm leaving.

635
00:47:34,770 --> 00:47:40,820
Sarah, I'll believe I have no kid then.

636
00:47:56,870 --> 00:48:00,390
Sarah... Jo Sarah.

637
00:48:03,640 --> 00:48:05,040
Mom.

638
00:48:05,040 --> 00:48:09,330
W-Who is that bastard?

639
00:48:09,330 --> 00:48:14,290
W-What was that bastard talking about?

640
00:48:14,290 --> 00:48:17,720
It's not true, is it? Is it?

641
00:48:17,720 --> 00:48:23,070
No. Everything he said was gibberish. Don't pay any mind to it.

642
00:48:23,070 --> 00:48:26,230
Hey, hey! Sarah! S-Sarah!

643
00:48:30,100 --> 00:48:32,400
Sarah! Open the door!

644
00:48:32,400 --> 00:48:33,810
Talk with me!

645
00:48:33,810 --> 00:48:35,080
Hey, Sarah!

646
00:48:35,080 --> 00:48:40,380
Mom, it's nothing. You misheard it, so don't worry about it.

647
00:48:40,380 --> 00:48:42,310
Sarah! Jo Sarah!

648
00:48:42,310 --> 00:48:44,870
Jo Sarah!

649
00:48:52,120 --> 00:48:54,400
Sarah, hey, Sarah. Open the door, please.

650
00:48:54,400 --> 00:48:57,540
Talk with me, please.

651
00:49:06,780 --> 00:49:08,770
Today's report.

652
00:49:08,770 --> 00:49:12,140
Jenny went to school from 8 AM to 4 PM,

