780
01:00:13,530 --> 01:00:16,660
I want to go home.

781
01:00:16,660 --> 01:00:20,290
Already?

782
01:00:20,290 --> 01:00:24,220
If you wait a bit, your favorite person will be here, Se Jong!

783
01:00:24,220 --> 01:00:26,220
Let's wait a moment.

784
01:00:26,220 --> 01:00:28,870
Hey, Sarah!

785
01:00:31,060 --> 01:00:33,400
Se Jong.

786
01:00:33,400 --> 01:00:39,420
Chief Jo, I want to go home.

787
01:00:39,420 --> 01:00:41,860
Chief Jo..?

788
01:00:41,860 --> 01:00:43,500
Oh, gosh...

789
01:00:43,500 --> 01:00:45,400
Yes, Se Jong, let's go.

790
01:00:45,400 --> 01:00:46,960
Hey.

791
01:00:46,960 --> 01:00:51,070
No...I mean, there's some ice cream left.

792
01:00:51,070 --> 01:00:52,930
I want to stop eating.

793
01:00:52,930 --> 01:00:55,940
I think I'll get a stomachache.

794
01:00:58,480 --> 01:01:02,760
Hey, this...this, what about all this then?

795
01:01:02,780 --> 01:01:06,930
Sarah! Hey, hey!

796
01:01:09,460 --> 01:01:15,510
I thought Grandma came to pick me up instead of Ms. Park.

797
01:01:15,510 --> 01:01:19,320
Today, Grandma was going to take Se Jong home...

798
01:01:19,320 --> 01:01:24,450
But Grandma had a lot of ice cream coupons!

799
01:01:24,450 --> 01:01:28,240
So she wanted to buy you ice creams, Se Jong.

800
01:01:28,240 --> 01:01:31,590
It's because you're so cute, Se Jong.

801
01:01:31,590 --> 01:01:35,320
- Ah, I see.
- Yes.

802
01:01:51,740 --> 01:01:54,250
Yes?

803
01:01:56,830 --> 01:01:59,470
Ms. Park.

804
01:01:59,470 --> 01:02:01,330
What about Se Jong?

805
01:02:01,330 --> 01:02:04,630
Se Jong just came home and washing his hands.

806
01:02:04,630 --> 01:02:08,060
Can we...talk for a moment?

807
01:02:08,060 --> 01:02:10,350
Sure.

808
01:02:13,450 --> 01:02:18,000
My mom took Se Jong today...

809
01:02:18,000 --> 01:02:24,520
because she had business near his kindergarten, and she was so delighted to see him.

810
01:02:24,520 --> 01:02:28,480
So she couldn't just go and had to buy him ice cream.

811
01:02:28,480 --> 01:02:32,390
My mom also has been very affectionate with him since he was a baby.

812
01:02:32,390 --> 01:02:36,640
Ah, I see...

813
01:02:36,640 --> 01:02:40,200
So, Ms. Park...

814
01:02:40,200 --> 01:02:45,440
What happened today... I'm hoping you won't report it to the Chairman.

815
01:02:45,440 --> 01:02:48,220
I'll report to him myself.

816
01:02:48,220 --> 01:02:52,690
I think there might be misunderstandings if I don't tell him directly,

817
01:02:52,690 --> 01:02:58,150
and my mom did that just because she was affectionate to Se Jong.

818
01:02:58,150 --> 01:03:01,670
Okay, I get it.

819
01:03:04,780 --> 01:03:07,180
Mom, are you mad?

820
01:03:07,180 --> 01:03:10,370
What kind of idiotic action was that!

821
01:03:10,370 --> 01:03:16,800
What is so wrong about me buying ice cream for my grandson?

822
01:03:16,800 --> 01:03:21,450
What have you done good, to be shouting at me?

823
01:03:21,450 --> 01:03:25,680
This is why I didn't tell you because I knew you'd act this way!

824
01:03:25,680 --> 01:03:30,420
Mom, I, no matter how I'd miss Se Jong!

825
01:03:30,420 --> 01:03:33,090
No matter how much I wanted to touch him!

826
01:03:33,090 --> 01:03:37,590
I held back and held back more!

827
01:03:37,590 --> 01:03:42,570
Mom! I...

828
01:03:42,590 --> 01:03:45,180
I held back for six years.

829
01:03:45,180 --> 01:03:48,010
For six years!

830
01:03:48,010 --> 01:03:49,970
Then why did you do that!

831
01:03:49,970 --> 01:03:53,610
Why?!

832
01:03:53,610 --> 01:03:59,730
Mom, if you can't hold yourself back right now, all my plans will fall apart, everything!

833
01:03:59,730 --> 01:04:02,170
Will it fall apart?

834
01:04:02,170 --> 01:04:06,570
Alright... Alright. I won't do that again.

835
01:04:06,570 --> 01:04:10,920
I won't go looking for him anymore.

836
01:04:15,550 --> 01:04:19,160
Oh, my poor baby...

837
01:04:19,160 --> 01:04:21,970
My poor baby...

838
01:04:25,490 --> 01:04:27,220
Today's report.

839
01:04:27,220 --> 01:04:32,610
Jenny and Se Chan returned from their school and tutoring without any issues at their usual time.

840
01:04:32,610 --> 01:04:36,610
Se Jong was picked up by Chief Jo today.

841
01:04:36,610 --> 01:04:39,170
Jenny and Se Chan finished their homework.

842
01:04:39,170 --> 01:04:45,500
And Jenny's grown brighter these days.

843
01:04:45,500 --> 01:04:48,540
Thank you for your good work. Rest well.

844
01:04:48,540 --> 01:04:52,910
Thank you! I hope you have a good night as well, Chairman.

845
01:05:01,100 --> 01:05:03,980
Yes, Noona?

846
01:05:03,980 --> 01:05:07,120
What? You're coming to Korea?

847
01:05:07,120 --> 01:05:09,690
When?

848
01:05:09,690 --> 01:05:12,390
Okay. I'll have your room cleaned.

849
01:05:12,390 --> 01:05:14,230
Ajumeoni.

850
01:05:14,230 --> 01:05:16,100
Oh, yes, Chairman? Do you need something?

851
01:05:16,100 --> 01:05:18,160
No, it's not that.

852
01:05:18,160 --> 01:05:21,990
There will be an important guest tomorrow, so can you prepare some food,

853
01:05:21,990 --> 01:05:24,440
and get the guest room ready?

854
01:05:24,440 --> 01:05:26,940
The guest room?

855
01:05:26,940 --> 01:05:32,550
Is it Ms. Anna Kim, who visited last time, coming?

856
01:05:32,550 --> 01:05:34,060
How did you know that?

857
01:05:34,060 --> 01:05:38,960
I knew it because your face is so bright, for the first time in a long while, Chairman!

858
01:05:38,960 --> 01:05:40,860
Then please take care of it.

859
01:05:40,860 --> 01:05:44,370
Ah, please make the marinated shrimp dish. You know that, right?

860
01:05:44,370 --> 01:05:46,410
Yes. Don't worry.

861
01:05:46,410 --> 01:05:50,900
I'll tell Mr. Park to go to the seafood market and buy some fresh shrimp in the morning.

862
01:05:50,900 --> 01:05:52,670
Thank you so much, Ajumeoni.

863
01:05:52,670 --> 01:05:54,850
Yes.

864
01:05:54,850 --> 01:05:59,640
Ms. Anna Kim's visiting in a while! What should I make more?

865
01:05:59,640 --> 01:06:02,120
Aren't you going to sleep?

866
01:06:02,120 --> 01:06:07,760
Oh, there will be an important guest from the States tomorrow! I was thinking about what I should make.

867
01:06:07,760 --> 01:06:09,800
An important guest?

868
01:06:09,800 --> 01:06:13,140
She's someone who's like a true older sister to our Chairman.

869
01:06:13,140 --> 01:06:15,560
She's the daughter of the nanny who raised the Chairman back then.

870
01:06:15,560 --> 01:06:19,650
She has a lot of our company's shares, and our Chairman cares a lot about her

871
01:06:19,650 --> 01:06:23,040
to the point Madam can't say anything to her either!

872
01:06:23,040 --> 01:06:25,260
I see.

873
01:06:28,310 --> 01:06:29,550
Ji Young!

874
01:06:29,550 --> 01:06:32,870
I feel suffocated. I feel like I'm going to die!

875
01:06:32,870 --> 01:06:34,190
This isn't living.

876
01:06:34,190 --> 01:06:37,810
It's like a prison! Like a cave without light!

877
01:06:37,810 --> 01:06:40,470
Just consider me dead!

878
01:06:40,470 --> 01:06:42,610
Ji Young! No!

879
01:06:42,610 --> 01:06:45,130
Please don't go!

880
01:06:45,130 --> 01:06:47,570
No!

881
01:06:50,470 --> 01:06:54,080
Are you okay? Did you have a nightmare?

882
01:06:54,100 --> 01:06:56,470
Huh?

883
01:06:56,470 --> 01:06:59,920
No. It's nothing.

884
01:06:59,920 --> 01:07:03,690
It's something!

885
01:07:03,690 --> 01:07:07,130
You're drenched in a cold sweat!

886
01:07:10,800 --> 01:07:17,450
You're having nightmares because we need to leave here soon.

887
01:07:21,850 --> 01:07:27,920
I find it hard to sleep peacefully too.

888
01:07:52,990 --> 01:07:55,880
[Welcome, Anna Kim]

889
01:08:00,230 --> 01:08:05,730
Are you from Chairman Lee Young Gook's company?

890
01:08:05,730 --> 01:08:09,080
Yes! Are you CEO Anna Kim?

891
01:08:09,080 --> 01:08:12,070
Yes. I'm Anna Kim--

892
01:08:17,210 --> 01:08:20,430
CEO!

893
01:08:27,390 --> 01:08:35,160
  Why do you run away, love, like a shy child 

894
01:08:35,160 --> 01:08:41,760
  In case I lose it, I hold it tight  

895
01:08:41,760 --> 01:08:49,010
  But love always runs away, chased by longing  

896
01:08:49,010 --> 01:08:55,810
  It would be nice to take a break  

897
01:08:55,810 --> 01:08:58,490
  I have to abandon the longing and the grieves  

898
01:08:58,490 --> 01:09:01,430
[Young Lady and Gentleman]

899
01:09:01,430 --> 01:09:04,530
He looks like him. He looks so much like Soo Chul Oppa.

900
01:09:04,530 --> 01:09:05,960
She's our teacher!

901
01:09:05,960 --> 01:09:08,130
Hello! Nice to meet you.

902
01:09:08,130 --> 01:09:11,330
What right do I have to think of Oppa and Dan Dan?

903
01:09:11,330 --> 01:09:12,330
Lee Jenny!

904
01:09:12,330 --> 01:09:13,900
Are you keeping tabs on me?

905
01:09:13,900 --> 01:09:16,060
What about you? What are you doing with a boy on the streets?

906
01:09:16,060 --> 01:09:17,700
Chairman, you're really hopeless.

907
01:09:17,700 --> 01:09:18,730
W-What?

908
01:09:18,730 --> 01:09:20,040
Isn't he Chairman Lee?

909
01:09:20,040 --> 01:09:21,910
W-Who the heck is she?

910
01:09:21,910 --> 01:09:23,590
The Chairman and Ms. Park?

911
01:09:23,590 --> 01:09:26,510
It seems like my son came to pick me up with his girlfriend!

912
01:09:26,510 --> 01:09:29,970
They'll all be so surprised when they realize I'm Se Ryun's mom!

913
01:09:29,970 --> 01:09:32,600
My Noona lives in this mansion? What happened?

914
01:09:32,600 --> 01:09:34,010
Isn't this the back of our house?

915
01:09:34,010 --> 01:09:35,450
What noise is this so late at night?

916
01:09:35,450 --> 01:09:36,700
Who are you!

917
01:09:36,700 --> 01:09:37,790
Ah! No!

918
01:09:37,790 --> 01:09:40,880
Ms. Park?
